And that leaves us a certain
amount of leeway for that.

00:41:47.300 --> 00:41:51.980
We have had romances
in the books.

00:41:51.980 --> 00:41:55.740
We are, however,
bitter and cynical men.

00:41:55.740 --> 00:42:05.270
And our views of how
love and sex interrelate

00:42:05.270 --> 00:42:09.030
may not fit gracefully with that
particular set of expectations.

00:42:11.247 --> 00:42:13.330
TY FRANCK: We're also
happily married, both of us,

00:42:13.330 --> 00:42:16.470
for like a really long time.

00:42:16.470 --> 00:42:19.005
And so our version of romance
is two people get together.

00:42:19.005 --> 00:42:20.130
they're nice to each other.

00:42:20.130 --> 00:42:22.090
And then they stay nice.

00:42:22.090 --> 00:42:25.025
Which is not really
compelling drama.

00:42:25.025 --> 00:42:27.400
DANIEL ABRAHAM: I have found
you, the woman of my dreams.

00:42:27.400 --> 00:42:29.450
Let's on the couch
and watch a movie.

00:42:29.450 --> 00:42:30.270
Ooh!

00:42:30.270 --> 00:42:31.384
TY FRANCK: Yeah, so--

00:42:31.384 --> 00:42:32.800
DANIEL ABRAHAM:
Not high conflict.

00:42:32.800 --> 00:42:34.891
TY FRANCK: Not a
lot of conflict.

00:42:34.891 --> 00:42:36.390
AUDIENCE: And yet
another question--

00:42:36.390 --> 00:42:37.770
will we ever see [INAUDIBLE]?

00:42:40.340 --> 00:42:43.170
TY FRANCK: That is a question
